      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "## Provision Compute Instance\n\nProvision a new compute instance with the specified instance type, cloud region, and OS image.\n\n### POST /v1/compute/provision\n\n#### Request Parameters\n\n| Parameter | Type | Description | Required |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| `instance_type` | string | The size of the VM to provision. | Yes |\n| `region` | string | The cloud region for deployment. | Yes |\n| `image_id` | string | The OS image to boot from. | Yes |\n\n#### Request Body\n\n* No request body is required for this operation.\n\n#### Response\n\n* The response will contain a resulting instance ID, which can be used to manage the instance.\n\n### Example Usage\n\n```bash\ncurl -X POST \\\n  https://cloudnexus.example.com/v1/compute/provision \\\n  -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \\\n  -d '{\"instance_type\": \"t2.micro\", \"region\": \"us-east-1\", \"image_id\": \"ami-12345678\"}'\n```\n\n#### HTTP Status Codes\n\n* 201 Created: The instance was successfully provisioned.\n* 400 Bad Request: The request was invalid or malformed.\n*",
